# Remote training credential surface — copy relevant values to actual files
#
# ALL of the files below are gitignored and must be mode 600.
# DO NOT put secrets inline in this file; this file documents what is needed.
#
# ─── Required files ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# ./hf_token
#   Hugging Face token with read access to dataset repos.
#   Obtain at: https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens
#   Usage: cat hf_token | head -c20   # should start with "hf_"
#
# ./gh_token
#   GitHub Personal Access Token (classic) with scope: write:packages
#   Obtain at: https://github.com/settings/tokens
#   Required for: docker login ghcr.io + making GHCR package public via gh api
#   If your org enforces SSO, also click "Authorize" next to your org after creation.
#
# ./secrets
#   Verda (DataCrunch) API credentials in the following format:
#     Secret: <your_client_secret>
#     CliendID : <your_client_id>
#   Obtain at: https://app.datacrunch.io/settings/api-credentials
#   Note: the "CliendID" typo in the Verda UI is preserved deliberately.
#
# ─── Optional files ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# ./gh_user
#   GitHub username override (e.g. "myorg" or "myuser").
#   If absent, the username is resolved via the GitHub API using gh_token
#   and cached to .omc/state/gh_user.cache.
#   Useful if you want to publish under an org namespace.
#
# ─── Runtime-generated (do not create manually) ──────────────────────────────
#
# .omc/state/gh_user.cache  — cached GitHub username
# .cf-tunnel.url            — ephemeral CF Quick Tunnel URL (created by run.sh remote)
# .cf-tunnel.pid            — cloudflared PID
# .cf-tunnel.log            — cloudflared stdout/stderr
# .dstack-server.log        — dstack server daemon log
# .run-ids                  — list of dstack run names created in current session
# artifacts-pull/           — pulled checkpoint artifacts (created with --pull-artifacts)
#
# ─── Environment variables injected by run.sh remote ─────────────────────────
#
# These are passed to the dstack task via the YAML env stanza; do NOT hardcode:
#
#   HF_TOKEN               — from ./hf_token
#   MLFLOW_TRACKING_URI    — from .cf-tunnel.url (ephemeral per run)
#   MLFLOW_EXPERIMENT_NAME — default: minimind-pretrain (override via env)
#   MLFLOW_ARTIFACT_UPLOAD — always 0 for remote runs (metrics only over tunnel)
#   VERDA_PROFILE          — set to "remote" for remote runs
#   IMAGE_SHA              — git short SHA of current HEAD
#   GH_USER                — from .omc/state/gh_user.cache or ./gh_user
